<taxonomicName authorityName="Lindroth" authorityYear="1976" box="[502,778,994,1018]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wanakense">
<emphasis box="[502,778,994,1018]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="47">Bembidion wanakense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the southern South Island (CO, DN, MK) sometimes have darker antennae and legs (antennal segment 1 piceous and tibiae black or piceous).
</paragraph>
